Celtic retained their seven-point lead at the top of Scottish Premiership with an easy 2-0 win over at Parkhead .
The home side laid siege to the Thistle defence at the start of the match but had to rely on a Kris Commons penalty .
Thistle midfielder James Craigen had been shown a straight red card by referee Willie Collum for a ` last man ' foul on Hoops midfielder Stuart Armstrong .
Stefan Johansen added a second in the 63rd minute .